<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEPARATING THE MEN FROM THE BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As an employee in the Hospitality Industry, I must chide S. Irene Virbila for 
her woefully outdated terminology ("The Drive Way," Restaurants, July 24). Does 
she realize, when mentioning the "busboy," that these workers are often grown 
men, many with wives and children? I find "busman" or "busser" to be far more 
appropriate. The era in which people referred to adults as "boys" is one I'm 
sure we all hope has long since come to a close. 
</P>
<P>
 ANGELINA MEANY 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
