<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALIENATED NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In response to Raul E. Acosta's letter (July 17), about Dr. Eva Carrizales and 
the death of her infant patient ("By a Doctor's Hand," by Barry Siegel, June 
12), I take issue with his statement, "As a Christian nation, it is our duty to 
uphold the idea that all life is sacred, and that we are to preserve it to the 
very last second." 
</P>
<P>
 First, who declared our nation to be a Christian one? What an insult to the 
citizens of this country who are of other religious persuasions. 
</P>
<P>
 And does the preservation of life to the very last second apply to those in 
the gas chamber or in the electric chair? 
</P>
<P>
 ANGELA S. LAIACONA 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
