<HEADLINE>
<P>
DELIGHTED BY DANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for Susan King's lovely retrospective of the stars from the recent 
past (TV Times, July 31). 
</P>
<P>
 I'm 74 and these people were so much a part of my growing up -- that is why I 
really appreciated the thoughtfulness of you remembering them. Especially Dana 
Andrews. While volunteering at the Democratic headquarters in the San Fernando 
Valley, I remember one afternoon answering phones. He called in for some 
information and we had a lovely conversation. 
</P>
<P>
 Thank you again for giving recognition to a group of people sometimes 
underrated and forgotten. 
</P>
<P>
 Lucille Garber, Van Nuys  
</P>
</TEXT>
