<TEXT>
<P>
 Mr. Klein (Bravo Sunday at 8 p.m., Monday at 8:30 a.m.) is Joseph Losey's dark 
1976 fable in which French art dealer Alain Delon exploits desperate Jews 
during World War II, only to meet an ironic fate. 
</P>
<P>
 Compromising Positions (Cinemax Thursday at 2 a.m.), a blithe 1985 
comedy-mystery, finds Joe Mantegna's lecherous dentist, the Lothario of Long 
Island, stabbed to death with one of his own dental instruments. One of his 
patients (Susan Sarandon) plays detective. 
</P>
