<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S MY LINE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In real life, George Gershwin said to Oscar Levant, "Upper berth, lower berth, 
that's the difference between talent and genius." 
</P>
<P>
 In the movie, "Rhapsody in Blue," the overnight train trip was filmed, but the 
comment was apparently deemed unsuitable for George to say, so Oscar was given 
the line. 
</P>
<P>
 JUNE LEVANT, LOS ANGELES 
