<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'I AM A FUGITIVE FROM A CHAIN GANG' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mervyn LeRoy's stark 1932 drama, based on a true story about an innocent man 
sent to a brutal prison only to escape and become a criminal, still retains its 
raw power. Both the lead actor, Paul Muni (pictured), and the film received 
Oscar nominations. This was a key movie in establishing Warner Bros. as 
Hollywood's most socially conscious -- and also liveliest -- studio in the '30s 
(Showtime Monday at 2:55 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
 Other four-star films airing this week: Beauty and the Beast Disney, Sunday, 7 
p.m.; Monday, 4:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Lives of a Bengal Lancer A&E, Wednesday, 1 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Jones Bravo, Wednesday, 7:30 p.m.; Thursday, 12:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Oliver Twist Showtime, Thursday, 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Gunga Din AMC, Saturday, 2 and 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sting TBS, Saturday, 7:05 p.m. Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</TEXT>
