<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: HUATULCO WEEK FITS TO A TEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A duffer's dream will come true at Huatulco's Club Med on Mexico's Pacific 
Coast when a special "Seniors Golf Week" is scheduled with nine golf teachers 
and professionals. Participants will spend one week in balmy Huatulco attending 
golf clinics, competing in chipping and putting contests, question-and-answer 
sessions, daily clinics and lessons. During the week, guests will play four 
18-hole rounds of golf as the pros roam the course offering playing tips and 
suggestions. The package includes carts, green fees and practice range balls. 
The final day features the Club Med Amateur Open Tournament with prizes awarded 
by the pros. 
</P>
<P>
 Seniors Golf Week is scheduled for Nov. 5-12. The price for the one-week stay 
in Huatulco, not including golf benefits, is $650 per person, double occupancy, 
including all meals, unlimited wine and beer at lunch and dinner, evening 
entertainment, picnics, boat rides and use of tennis courts. A surcharge of 
$150 is levied for guests over age 55 who participate in the golf program. 
Those under 55 pay $300. Price does not include transportation to and from 
Huatulco. Grandchildren ages 4 to 12, who come with one paying adult, are 
welcome at no extra charge including all meals. For information, call weekdays 
from 6 a.m. to 6 p.m., weekends 6 a.m. to 1 p.m. Telephone: (800) 258-2633. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 TLC, a company that specializes in tours for seniors, is offering day trips to 
Nevada state-line casinos, as well as longer tours featuring theater 
presentations and special events. There are two- to four-day trips to Las 
Vegas, Laughlin, Lake Tahoe and Reno. Motor-coach trips with per-person prices 
based on double occupancy include: $60 for two nights at the Flamingo Hilton in 
Laughlin; $30 for one night at the Fremont in Las Vegas and $135 for three 
nights at the Reno Hilton. TLC's longer tours include an eight-night Cajun 
Dixie tour to the historic South, which includes some meals and round-trip air 
transportation from Los Angeles for $1,199 per person. 
</P>
<P>
 A free three-month membership includes a copy of their monthly publication. 
Regular membership is $5; tel. (800) 300-1852. 
</P>
</TEXT>
