<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOW'S THAT AGAIN? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was reassuring to learn ("Travel Insider," July 24) that Metro Rail won't 
be connecting to LAX because (airport and Federal Aviation Administration 
officials said that) "the Green Line's path could distract pilots with its 
lights, befuddle radar with electromagnetic emissions and stand in the way of 
low-flying aircraft in emergencies." Quick! Will someone please inform airport 
officials in London, Frankfurt, Chicago, Dallas-Fort Worth and all those other 
progressive cities that they might be in danger? And to think I was blaming the 
taxi lobby. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT LERNER, Valley Center 
</P>
</TEXT>
