Travel; Part L; Page 26; Column 3; Travel Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
87 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DATA FOR DUDES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As an avid dude ranch vacationer, I read "Say Howdy Dude" (July 17) with 
considerable interest. The two ranches you covered were both large in terms of 
guest capacity; there are many ranches that accommodate 30 or fewer, and these 
have a distinctly different feeling, marked by a far more flexible structure. 
Also, Eugene Kilgore's "Ranch Vacations," distributed by John Muir 
publications, is an excellent source on dude ranches, fly fishing ranches and 
cross-country skiing ranches. 
</P>
<P>
 LESLIE GOLDENBERG, Los Angeles 
</P>
