</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: The conservative country music world is the last place 
you'd expect to find a film director best known for steamy sex scenes. But 
Zalman King, whose credits include "9 1/2 Weeks" and "Wild Orchid," has filmed 
a 30-second TV commercial for country singer John Berry. 
</P>
<P>
 "Country singers sing about all this stuff -- they just don't show it," says 
Berry of the romantic content of the clip, which features him and a sultry 
female love interest to the tune of his "Your Love Amazes Me," a No. 1 country 
hit this year.  
</P>
<P>
 In truth, the clip tells its short story more through inference than actual 
visuals. 
</P>
<P>
 "The song is quite romantic, and even though John and the woman never get 
together, you feel a tremendous longing between them," says King, who is 
finishing work on his next film, "Delta of Venus," based on an Anais Nin erotic 
story, which he expects to get an NC-17 rating. 
</P>
<P>
 Asked about the teaming, Bob Freese, Liberty Records' vice president of sales 
and marketing, says, "We were looking for something outside the norm to help 
people get to know John better."* 
</P>
