<P>
SARATOGA FAVORITE IS SIDELINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fourstardave, the 9-year-old gelding who has become an institution in Saratoga 
racing, is finished for the year. 
</P>
<P>
 He severely sprained his left ankle turning for home in Friday's running of 
the Bernard Baruch Handicap, in which he finished third. Fourstardave was 
leading coming into the stretch, but was passed with a furlong to go by Lure, 
the eventual winner, and Paradise Creek. 
</P>
