<HEADLINE>
<P>
THAT'S NO WAY TO REWARD A BRAVE ACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The story regarding a customer firing at a bank robber ("Customer, Fleeing 
Bank Robber Exchange Gunfire," Aug. 6) illustrates clearly why crime is 
evident. 
</P>
<P>
 A brave citizen acts against an armed criminal who has just committed a felony 
and for his good deed and courage is arrested and charged with three crimes: 
carrying a concealed weapon, discharging a firearm, and delaying the 
investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 If eventually acquitted, he will probably be in hock to the legal profession 
for a couple of years' pay. 
</P>
<P>
 California's laws are a marvelous protection for the criminal. Many folks who 
have the courage to risk their lives by acting against crime are deterred by 
the near certainty of losing their savings and quite possibly homes and jobs 
through the action of our legal systems. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN T. FOOTE 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
