<P>
HOUSING: CITY CHARTER AND NEW HOPE PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The article of July 17 about project New Hope ("How A Good Idea Became a 
Political Hot Potato") left the reader with the notion that the (Santa Monica) 
City Council could use the parcel in question for something other than on-site, 
affordable housing. It should have been made clear that replacing the 11 
affordable units previously there was mandated by the city's charter. Debate 
about open space, parkland, commercial use, luxury housing or any other use on 
this site must begin with that fact. 
</P>
