<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCEAN DROWNING VICTIM IDENTIFIED AS ALASKA RESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 47-year-old man who drowned in the ocean near Dana Point Harbor was 
identified Saturday as Ronald Petros of Anchorage, Alaska. 
</P>
<P>
 Petros was swimming about 30 yards off a rock jetty near the harbor with his 
18- and 15-year-old sons about 3 p.m. Friday, when the trio became caught in a 
riptide, said an Orange County Sheriff's Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 A 911 call from a witness sent a Dana Point Harbor Patrol launch to the area 
and all three swimmers were rescued, but Petros was later declared dead at a 
local hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Petros had been visiting relatives in Laguna Hills with his wife and children, 
according to a spokesman at the Orange County coroner's office. 
</P>
