<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUCK RUNS OFF I-5 INTO DITCH, KILLING DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 38-year-old truck driver was killed early Saturday when he apparently fell 
asleep at the wheel of his big-rig and drove off an embankment, the California 
Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities believe the accident occurred about midnight, but it was not 
discovered until about six hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, whose name was not released pending notification of his death to 
relatives, was traveling south on Interstate 5 near the Junipero Serra Road 
exit when he apparently fell asleep and drifted down an embankment into a dirt 
ditch, a CHP spokeswoman said. He was killed on impact. 
</P>
