<P>
LOCAL NOTES; SOCAL WATER POLO WINS THREE TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SoCal, the Tustin-based water polo club, swept the national Junior Olympic 
championships, winning the 13-and-under, 15-and-under and 17-and-under 
divisions Saturday at Long Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 David Hay scored four goals and most-valuable-player Sam Grayeli scored two as 
the 17-and-under team beat Annapolis (Md.), 8-6.Hay, a Foothill graduate, will 
attend Stanford; Grayeli, a Costa Mesa graduate, will attend USC. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 15-and-under division, MVP Brian Brown of Foothill High scored two 
goals in a 4-2 victory over Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 13-and-under division, MVP Robby Arroyo, who will be a freshman at 
Foothill, scored six goals in a 14-1 victory over Cerritos. Nick Pacelli of 
Villa Park scored five. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Tustin Bobby Sox softball team playing in the national tournament for 10- 
and 11-year olds in Sparks, Nev., beat Roseville, 9-1, in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin had beaten Koolaw of Hawaii, 9-1, Friday. Tustin plays Sparks, which is 
also 2-0 in the tournament, today. 
</P>
