<P>
BOONE'S MILL EASILY WINS SAPLING STAKES FOR LUKAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Boone's Mill and jockey Pat Day drew off through the stretch for a 5 
3/4-length victory in the $200,000 Sapling Stakes at Monmouth Park on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Enlighten was second, two lengths in front of Western Echo. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory marked the fourth time in the last six years trainer Wayne Lukas 
has saddled the winner of the Sapling. 
</P>
<P>
