<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN SHOT DEAD IN HER LIVING ROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JILL BETTNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 38-year-old Palmdale woman was shot and killed in the living room of her 
home Friday night, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies were called to the couple's home in the 
37700 block of Cottonwood Street shortly before 10 p.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, TeriLynn Peitz, was dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Deputy Dianne Hecht said Saturday that Peitz's husband told 
detectives an intruder entered the couple's house, shot his wife and fled, 
Hecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives had no additional information about the alleged intruder or the 
circumstances surrounding the shooting. Hecht said neighbors of the couple had 
not reported seeing the suspect. 
</P>
<P>
 Hecht said the investigation by the Sheriff's Department is continuing. She 
declined to say whether the murdered woman's husband was also a possible 
suspect in the killing. JILL BETTNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
