<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; BYSTANDERS COME TO AID OF ROBBERY VICTIM, 75 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bystanders came to the rescue of a 75-year-old man who was robbed as he walked 
to church Saturday, capturing the teen-age suspect, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Donathan was walking on North Ventura Avenue around 11:30 a.m. on his way 
to the Avenue Community Church when the teen-ager ran up behind him and yanked 
Donathan's wallet out of his back pocket, said senior pastor Clifford Musgrove, 
who witnessed the incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "Paul's just a little guy, and he couldn't really fight back," Musgrove said. 
"But everybody knows Paul around here and everybody loves him. Not two seconds 
later, three men went after that boy and caught him." 
</P>
<P>
 The men wrestled the youth to the ground and held him until police arrived, 
Musgrove said. Meanwhile, other witnesses picked up Donathan's wallet, which 
the youth had thrown under a car, and returned it to him, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donathan, a retired Ventura city employee who has a pacemaker, was shaken but 
unhurt, police said. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
