<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARIES; WILLIAM GROSSBACH; ASSISTANT SCHOOLS CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 William Grossbach, a former Ventura County assistant superintendent of 
schools, has died at age 72. 
</P>
<P>
 Grossbach served as county assistant superintendent for business services from 
1973 to 1987.During that time, he was a driving force in establishing 
self-funded insurance programs for all of Ventura County's 21 school districts, 
said James F. Cowan, who was a county superintendent of schools during 
Grossbach's tenure. 
</P>
<P>
 From 1979 to 1987, Grossbach also served as the president of the Ventura 
County Schools Self-Funding Authority, a coalition made up of the county's 
public school districts. Through the self-funded insurance programs, the 
authority freed money for educational programs while still providing 
significant levels of coverage for workers compensation, liability and other 
forms of self-insurance, authority officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowan said county school districts shared resources under the self-funded 
insurance programs to lower their insurance costs. 
</P>
<P>
 "It enabled the schools to save considerable money in terms of their various 
insurance premiums, enabling that money to flow right into the classroom," 
Cowan said. 
</P>
<P>
 Grossbach, a native of Minnesota and a former resident of Ventura, was living 
in Sacramento at the time of his death. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 McReynolds, Larry, 44, of Newbury Park, concrete finisher. Pierce Brothers 
Griffin Mortuary, Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County obituaries are published free of charge as a public service to 
readers. Obituaries are based on information provided by mortuaries. 
</P>
