<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOST UNFORGETTABLE APPRAISAL OF A HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In defense of Robert J. Bruss on appraisers and appraisals, here is the most 
unforgettable appraisal I ever saw: 
</P>
<P>
 Several years ago, I requested a copy of the appraisal from a company that was 
trying to sell me a second-trust deed. The independent appraisal showed a 
two-story house of sizable square footage in Laguna Beach with a high value.A 
drive to the address showed a one-story bungalow in then-unlivable condition, 
with two guys on the roof hammering away in after-work hours on what might have 
been the gleam of a second story in the owner's eye. 
</P>
<P>
 No, I didn't report the appraiser to the licensing bureau, although I should 
have. And no, it is not the only dubious appraisal I ever received. And yes, I 
do think most appraisers are ethical and conscientious. 
</P>
<P>
 BLANCHE THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
 Lake Forest 
</P>
