<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CENTRAL: DOWNTOWN; APARTMENT OWNER TO FACE SLUM CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 38-year-old Encino man is scheduled to be arraigned Thursday in Los Angeles 
Municipal Court on 22 counts of slum violations at his South Hope Street 
apartment building, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Youdai and his company, Advance Project Management Inc., were named on 
the misdemeanor complaint filed by the city attorney's office last month, said 
Deputy City Atty. Lawrence P.V. Punter. The charges were filed after the city's 
housing task force inspected the building at 1355 S. Hope St. between May 2 and 
June 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Inside the four-story, 56-room brick apartment complex, inspectors discovered 
rodent and cockroach infestations, defective plumbing, missing and defective 
smoke detectors and damaged walls, the deputy city attorney said. Youdai could 
not be reached for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
